-- Latvia’s Population Fell 13% in the Past Decade, BNS Reports
-- B y   A a r o n   E g l i t i s
-- 2012-01-18T08:51:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/latvia-s-population-fell-13-in-the-past-decade-bns-reports.html
Latvia ’s population fell 13 percent
in the last 10 years, the Baltic news Service reported, citing
the  Central Statistics Office .  The number of people living in Latvia fell to 2,067,887,
according to provisional data from a census carried out last
year, BNS said. Revised census data will be released later this
year, according to the Riga-based newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Eglitis in Riga at 
 aeglitis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
